cs.MA, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI

The paper proposes a nature-inspired approach to optimize the movements of an UAV swarm towards maintaining communication between the ground agents. This involves the use of swarm intelligence and evolutionary computation. The paper also models the ground agents and the UAVs as boids-based swarms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also involves the use of evolutionary computation, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the coordination of UAVs, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the optimization of network survivability, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of an on-line real-time Genetic Algorithm, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
